 Hubble expansion and the redshift are\naccounted for by a continuing slow increase in n. Comparison with experimental\ndata suggests that the rate of increase must be at least one n unit every 30-60\nmillion years.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Oct 2004 18:51:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 Oct 2004 19:40:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
